  <h2 id="exit-codes">Exit codes</h2>
  <p>All commands follow the same convention:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>0</code> — success</li>
    <li><code>1</code> — error (Cobra's default; prints error message to stderr)</li>
    <li><code>130</code> — interrupted (Ctrl+C)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="summary">Summary</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>39 primary commands</strong> across 14 categories. All are implemented in the current release.
    4 commands are hidden from <code>-h</code> (<code>route approve/reject</code>, <code>route approve-exit-node/reject-exit-node</code>)
    — still callable, but admin-only on the backend.
    1 command is a thin stub (<code>licenses</code> — redirects to the website).
    Everything else is full-featured with proper error handling, JSON output, and multi-platform support (Linux, macOS, Windows; amd64 and arm64).
  </p>
